      • label

        public static <T> util.object.Either<java.lang.String,T> label(java.lang.String errorMsgPrefix,
                                                               util.object.Either<java.lang.String,T> value)
        Prefixes the error message (i.e. any left value) with the specified label p so that if e is the original message, the new message will be of the form p:e.
        Type Parameters:
        T - any type.
        Parameters:
        errorMsgPrefix - the string to prefix to the error message.
        value - the input to prefix in the case it's a left value.
        Returns:
        the prefixed error message if the input either is a left value; otherwise the input's right value as is.
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if any argument is null.
